It is meant to be.

01:15:03.530 --> 01:15:05.451
I mean, before I knew about tool calling,

01:15:05.451 --> 01:15:07.011
I would hear about people saying like,

01:15:07.011 --> 01:15:09.650
oh, what if these AIs take over the world?

01:15:09.650 --> 01:15:10.771
What if we're building Skynet

01:15:10.771 --> 01:15:12.331
and it decides to turn on its makers?

01:15:12.331 --> 01:15:13.850
And I'm like, what are you talking about?

01:15:13.850 --> 01:15:16.090
Like you are talking about a chat bot.

01:15:16.090 --> 01:15:17.771
You give it questions, it gives you answers.

01:15:17.771 --> 01:15:20.571
How could something like that take over the world?

01:15:20.571 --> 01:15:21.931
And then I learned about tool calling

01:15:21.931 --> 01:15:23.850
and I was like, oh, that's how, okay.

01:15:23.850 --> 01:15:25.650
That's how.

01:15:25.650 --> 01:15:30.650
And people, I gotta say like people are going pretty nuts

01:15:30.970 --> 01:15:35.491
giving these LLMs access to pretty unfettered tools.

01:15:35.491 --> 01:15:40.290
Like here's a computer, like take control of my computer,

01:15:40.290 --> 01:15:41.931
take control of a web browser.

01:15:43.090 --> 01:15:46.891
And fortunately, most of the better LLMs these days,

01:15:47.131 --> 01:15:52.011
they are quite, by default, they really try to behave well

01:15:52.011 --> 01:15:53.730
and not do scary things.

01:15:54.730 --> 01:15:57.331
But you can totally see how you would get

01:15:57.331 --> 01:16:00.290
to a Skynet scenario eventually.

01:16:00.290 --> 01:16:02.290
Yeah, so meant to be a little bit scary.

